annotationA: G2/mitotic-specific cyclin-B; Cyclin B (CycB) binds to Cdk1, thereby promoting Cdk1's protein kinase activity. The complex CycB-Cdk1 complex induces the start of mitosis. During late metaphase of mitosis and continuing in G1, CycB is rapidly degraded (involving APC/C and the proteasome), resulting in inactivation of Cdk1 protein kinase activity, and allowing termination of mitosis
annotationB: Cyclin H homolog; RNA polymerase II carboxy-terminal domain kinase activity; protein kinase binding; core RNA polymerase binding transcription factor activity; cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity; cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase regulator activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; regulation of transcription, DNA-templated; regulation of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity; transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
